Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.47,0:05:36.61,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它看起来只是天空上一颗小小的红色星球 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It appears as nothing more than a tiny red orb in our night sky 
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.56,0:05:42.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,尽管如此 几百年来 火星还是迷惑了人们 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Even so, Mars has captivated human kind for centuries 
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.09,0:05:54.48,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它的名字取自罗马战神的名字 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The planet takes its name from the Roman God of war 
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.99,0:06:03.31,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,罗马人将战争和动荡和这个遥远的地方联系在一起 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Romans associated this distant world with ostility and unrest,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.46,0:06:08.23,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是因为它那血一般的颜色 而且还因为它在天上与众不同的运动 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because of its blood-like colour, and because of its distinctive movement in the sky 
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.24,0:06:13.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,火星奇迹 它不会做其他星球做的事情 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Mars wonders It doesn't do what the stars do 
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.09,0:06:23.11,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,红色星球有时会在天上向后移动 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The red planet occasionally appears to be moving backward across the sky 
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.36,0:06:26.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其举止迷惑了观察者几百年 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A behavior that confounded observers for centuries 
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.15,0:06:30.67,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然而在1514年 深入研究了这颗行星的运动后 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But in 1514, close study of this planetary movement,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.90,0:06:33.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,顶尖的波兰天文学家哥白尼\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lead Polish astronomer Nicholas Copernicus
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.40,0:06:36.62,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,革命性地定义了太阳系 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to a revolutionary understanding of the solar system 
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.00,0:06:43.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在许多有记录的历史上 人们认为地球是宇宙的中心 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}For much of recording history, people thought that Earth was at the center of the Universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.82,0:06:49.19,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,接着来了哥白尼 他说道 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Along come Copernicus, and he says?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.29,0:06:52.02,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不 地球不可能是宇宙的中心 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}No, maybe the Earth isn't at the center of the Universe 
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.43,0:06:56.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,物体围绕着太阳运行也许可以解释这一切 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Maybe the explanation for all this is that, things are going around the Sun 
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.50,0:07:01.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果行星围绕着太阳运行 那么我们能够解释为什么\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And if all the planets are going around the Sun, then we can explain why
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.96,0:07:04.34,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当地球越过在轨的火星时 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as Earth passes Mars in the orbit,
