Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.37,0:14:44.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,水当然是一份氧和两份氢组成的 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Water of course is one part oxygen and two parts hydrogen,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.25,0:14:49.19,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以冰可能覆盖在那些区域的地表之下是无可辩驳的 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so the possibility of ice hiding below the surface in those areas is overwhelming 
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.96,0:14:56.07,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而在火星极地有冰存在的明显证据 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But while strong evidence of ice at the martian poles may be relatively new
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.17,0:15:01.45,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那里存在着水 会联想到一个世纪前普遍认为的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}speculation that water existed there became common more than a century ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.51,0:15:08.64,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,红色星球上也存在着智能生命 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and its implication that intelligent life could also exist on the red planet,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.74,0:15:11.36,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在地球上引起广泛的盼望 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}elicited wide spread anxiety on Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.46,0:15:14.74,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,特别是在20世纪前半个世纪 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for much of the first half of the twentieth century 
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.09,0:15:23.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,天文学家在1610年首次将望远镜指向火星 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Astronomers pointed the first telescope towards Mars in 1610 
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.09,0:15:28.81,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,随着望远镜技术的不断改进 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As spyglass technology steadily improved,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.91,0:15:30.64,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,红色星球模糊的印象\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a blurred image of the red planet
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.74,0:15:34.50,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,比过去任何时候更靠近地球观察员的眼睛 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}drew ever closer to the eyes of earthly observers 
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.37,0:15:40.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在1877年 望远镜能够放大远方行星的映象 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}By 1877 telescopes could enlarge the image of the distant planet,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.47,0:15:45.06,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以能够大致看清远方的东西 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so that it appeared roughly the size of a dime held at harm's length 
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.48,0:15:48.14,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当然按现代标准算不得什么 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Certainly not impressive by modern standards,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.24,0:15:51.14,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但对米兰天文台台长来说已经足够了 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but it was enough for the director of the Milano observatory,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.24,0:15:52.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,乔伐尼·齐亚巴雷利 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Giovanni Schiaparelli,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.92,0:15:57.41,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,努力勾勒火星表面 对其地貌进行命名 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to attempt to sketch the martian surface and name its geological features 
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.30,0:16:01.15,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,齐亚巴雷利窥视那朦胧多变的映象 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Schiaparelli peered at the hazy shifty visage
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.25,0:16:03.60,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,几个月里一晚接着一晚 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}night after night for months 
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.93,0:16:10.42,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他看到了火星表面他认为的十字交叉线 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And he sees what he thinks are criss-cross lines on the surface of Mars 
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.56,0:16:13.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,后来证明 他看到的不完全是那里有什么 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It turns out later, what he saw isn't exactly
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.83,0:16:17.57,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是通过他那粗糙的望远镜还是能看到什么的 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}what's up there, but still through his crude telescope that's what he could see 
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.58,0:16:21.80,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,尊敬的意大利天文学家勾画了这些线条\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Respected italian astronomers sketched these lines
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.64,0:16:24.23,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,并给它们取了名字 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and gave them a name 
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.70,0:16:28.41,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,齐亚巴雷利认为那些线条象\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Schiaparelli interpreted these lines as
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.58,0:16:31.05,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,某种河床 他并不真的了解 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}channels of some sort, he didn't really know 
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.16,0:16:34.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在这 他用意大利语称它们是"canali" \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Well, the italian word that he applied to them was "canali",
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.00,0:16:39.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那个词 翻译成英语应该译成"河床"(channels) \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that word, translated to english should have been translated as "channels",
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.48,0:16:42.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是相反被误译成"运河"(canals) \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but instead it got mistranslated as "canals" 
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.50,0:16:48.45,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,由于自然界没有看到过直线 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Since straight lines do not normally appear in nature,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.55,0:16:51.13,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,齐亚巴雷利勾画的时候产生了念头\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Schiaparelli sketches gave birth to the idea
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.23,0:16:55.16,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,即火星上应该存在智能生命的某种形态 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that some form of intelligent life must exist on Mars 
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.46,0:16:58.16,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是一个引人瞩目的想法 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It was an arresting notion,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.26,0:17:01.19,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,天文学家一直为之广泛辩论 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}widely debated among the astronomers of the day 
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.23,0:17:07.19,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,后来在1894年 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Later in 1894,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.29,0:17:10.01,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一个叫帕西瓦尔 罗威尔的波士顿富人\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a wealthy Bostonian named Percival Lowell
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.11,0:17:12.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,竟然被这个想法吸引 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}was so intrigued by this possibility
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.47,0:17:16.06,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,买了大望远镜安放在\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that he paid to have a large telescope constructed on a mountain side
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.16,0:17:18.06,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,亚利桑那州旗杆市的山旁 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in Flagstaff, Arizona 
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.46,0:17:22.48,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他化了接下来的20年对红色星球进行观察 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He spent the next two decades observing, sketching
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.57,0:17:25.51,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,勾画和推测 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and speculating about the red planet 
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.91,0:17:33.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他自信已经看到火星上直线组成的网络 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He convinced himself that he was seeing networks of straight lines on Mars,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.02,0:17:35.66,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他认为那就是运河 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which he thought were canals,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.76,0:17:37.95,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在那些日子里和巴拿马运河一起成为大新闻 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}what was the big news at the day with the Panama canal,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.05,0:17:41.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那是伟大的行星文明创造的 他们建造了运河 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that's what great planetary civilisations do, they build canals 
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.66,0:17:50.67,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以这是火星上从极地冰帽引水的运河 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So this was canals to bring the water down from the polar ice caps on Mars,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.87,0:17:53.86,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,由于是寒冷 远离太阳 还是干燥 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which are cold and far from the Sun and dry,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.96,0:17:55.78,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以他知道 所以他认为 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so he knew that and so he thought,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.88,0:17:58.71,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好了 在火星上他们必须为了生活运水 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}well, they have to move the water to live on Mars 
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.89,0:18:03.24,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那个想法正好刺激了每个人 火星上有个文明 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That idea just electrified everybody, that there was a civilisation on Mars 
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.03,0:18:12.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在此背景下 1938年万圣节的晚上 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Against this backdrop on Halloween night 1938
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.13,0:18:15.13,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一个名叫奥森·威尔斯的年轻播音员\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A young actor named Orson Wells
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.13,0:18:18.36,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,推出了[世界大战]的广播剧 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}broadcasted a dramatisazion of War of the Worlds
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.55,0:18:21.45,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一部英国作家H G 威尔斯的小说 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A novella by british author H G Wells
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.62,0:18:25.19,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,描写险恶的火星人登陆地球 并进行肆虐 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In which sinister martians land on Earth and wreak havoc
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.39,0:18:29.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们把你带回Grovers磨房的卡尔·菲利普斯那里 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We now return you to Carl Phillips at Grovers Mill 
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.95,0:18:32.92,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,女士们 先生们 我在这里等一会儿 发生了一些情况\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}ladies and gentlemen, here I am wait a minute, something's happening
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.61,0:18:36.35,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有一架飞机从那镜子弹出 跳在那路人的右边\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There's a plane springing from that mirror and it leaps right at the advancing men
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.35,0:18:38.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,好家伙 他们变成了火焰!\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Good Lord, they're turning into flame!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.24,0:18:45.58,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,成千上万的市民认为这是真的入侵 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Thousands of citizens believed the invasion was real 
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.68,0:18:52.10,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我对此深深地感到震惊和哀悼 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I'm deeply shocked and deeply regret for,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.36,0:18:54.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,误会是短暂的 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The misunderstanding was short lived 
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.82,0:18:59.19,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然而即便如此 广播只是给大众关于火星上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But even so the broadcast only served to fuel public speculation
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.32,0:19:02.50,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可能存在智能生命的猜想添油加醋 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}about potential intelligent life on Mars 
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.21,0:19:16.47,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,火星:吸引着人类数千年 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Mars: it has intrigued human kind for thousands of years 
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.92,0:19:18.59,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,20世纪中期 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And in mid 20th century
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.59,0:19:22.55,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,人类终于近距离地观察神秘的行星 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}humans finally got a closer look at the mysterious planet 
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.61,0:19:34.50,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,1964年 美国航空航天局 NASA \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In 1964 the National Aeronautic and Space Admininstration, NASA,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.54,0:19:38.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,向红色星球发射了小探险飞船 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}launched the small exploration spacecraft toward the red planet
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.93,0:19:47.29,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它的名字叫做水手4号 带有一个电视摄像机 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Its name was Mariner 4, it had a television camera
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.29,0:19:50.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它的使命是飞过火星 传回图象 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and its mission was to fly past Mars and send back pictures 
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.76,0:19:53.67,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它只能经过一次 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It could only make one pass 
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.22,0:20:02.94,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,科学家伴随着激动 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Scientists were filled with anxious excitement
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.95,0:20:05.45,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,充满了期待 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}at the prospect of what they might see 
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.81,0:20:11.66,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,将会看到城市？将会看到运河？将会看到森林？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Well it is gonna see cities, is it gonna see canals, is it gonna see forests?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.37,0:20:14.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然而所有能看到的都是弹坑 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But all of what it saw it was craters 
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.75,0:20:21.68,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,飞船发回的图象只是非常模糊 弹坑看上去就象月亮上的一样 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It sent back pictures which just were very fuzzy and showed craters like on the moon 
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.79,0:20:25.54,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是一个巨大的失望 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It was a huge let down 
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.92,0:20:30.66,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,水手4号的图象显示了一个干燥多坑的沙漠的情景 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Mariner 4 images revealed a dry cratered desert like
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.66,0:20:32.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,表面死寂的行星 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and seemingly dead planet 
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.23,0:20:37.13,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有点象月亮 一点空气吹着周围的沙尘 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Sort of like the moon with a little air to blow the dust around 
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.10,0:20:41.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是探索火星的热情只是被降温 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But the enthusiasm for exploring Mars was only tempered 
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.88,0:20:48.58,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,6年后 在1971年 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And 6 years later, in 1971,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.58,0:20:52.66,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,NASA向红色星球发射了另一艘飞船:水手9号 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NASA sent another spacecraft to the red planet: Mariner 9 
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.19,0:20:59.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是这时 舍弃了仅仅经过火星 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But this time, rather than just making a single pass by Mars
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.96,0:21:03.15,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,水手9号被制造成围绕火星几个星期 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Mariner 9 was engineered to orbit the planet for weeks
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.15,0:21:05.01,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,做一个完整的扫描 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and do a complete mapping 
